

## Executive Summary

Suspicious network activity was detected on endpoint "oficina-ventas". A repetitive HTTPS connection pattern was observed every 10 seconds for approximately 2 hours. The activity occurred after the execution of a downloaded executable file.

## Detection

The incident was identified through network traffic analysis.

Indicators:
- HTTPS traffic (443)
- Repetition every 10 seconds
- Duration of 2 hours
- No user interaction

## Technical Analysis

IP:
- 185.243.115.23

Domain:
- update-check-service.net

Observed Pattern:
- Persistent communication
- Constant interval
- Automated behavior

Behavior Classification:
- Possible Command and Control (C2) Beaconing

## Risk Assessment

Risk Level: HIGH

The observed behavior is consistent with potential C2 communications and may indicate active compromise of the endpoint.

## Immediate Actions

- Isolate affected endpoint
- Block malicious IP
- Block suspicious domain
- Review persistence mechanisms
- Inspect additional endpoints

## Conclusion

The system shows indicators consistent with potential C2 activity. Immediate containment and investigation are recommended.
